    <!-- ============================================
         02. BIO
         ============================================ -->
    <section id="bio" class="bio">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="section-num">02</span>
                <h2 class="section-title">Bio</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="bio-grid">
                <div class="bio-sidebar">
                    Full Biography<br>
                    [Word Count: ~350]<br><br>
                    For Press Use<br>
                    <a href="mailto:micahweekes@hotmail.com" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--black);">Request PDF ↓</a>
                </div>

                <div class="bio-body">
                    <p>
                        Micah Weekes is a pianist, composer, and educator based in Toronto, Canada. 
                        His musical foundation was laid early at the Suzuki School of Music in North York, 
                        where he began formal piano training as a child. By age eight, he had taken up 
                        playing in church — a practice he continues to this day, and one that has 
                        profoundly shaped his harmonic language and sense of groove.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Weekes' first serious immersion in jazz came through Jazz.FM91's Youth Seminar Band, 
                        a nationally recognized training program run by one of Canada's premier jazz radio stations. 
                        He remained in the ensemble for two years, developing his improvisational voice and 
                        ensemble skills alongside peers from across the region. Shortly after, he was admitted 
                        to the University of Toronto's Bachelor of Music in Jazz Piano Performance program 
                        on a full scholarship — an acknowledgment of both his technical ability and his 
                        artistic potential.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Since graduating, Weekes has established himself as a fixture of Toronto's jazz scene, 
                        performing regularly at venues including the Jazz Bistro, The Rex, The Emmet Ray, 
                        and The Pilot, among others. His work spans solo piano, small ensemble leadership, 
                        and sideman roles, with a repertoire that moves fluidly between standards, original 
                        compositions, and exploratory improvisational sets.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Currently, Weekes is focused on expanding his compositional output, writing new 
                        material for both piano and organ while continuing to refine his performance practice. 
                        His work reflects a musician equally at home in the tradition and in the process of 
                        pushing it forward — grounded, curious, and committed to the craft.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

